hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I love the theatre enlast australia The heat index of the South Carolina summer is heightened when you walk past the rows of bulk barns in the process of drying the crop for market. The green tobacco is loaded in the barns and kept for a week in constant heat and airflow. The process changes the crop from a green odorless crop to a milky brown colored leaf. The sweet smell of the cured leaf dangles around at the top of your nose and almost makes you forget that cigarettes, the crops end product, can be dangerous to your health. After the tobacco is cured, it is covered and taken to the nearby market center for sale and grading.
